    19вҶ’
    20вҶ’**mdBook** is a command line tool to create books with Markdown.
    21вҶ’It is ideal for creating product or API documentation, tutorials, course materials or anything that requires a clean,
    22вҶ’easily navigable and customizable presentation.
    23вҶ’
    24вҶ’* Lightweight [Markdown] syntax helps you focus more on your content
    25вҶ’* Integrated [search] support
    26вҶ’* Color [syntax highlighting] for code blocks for many different languages
    27вҶ’* [Theme] files allow customizing the formatting of the output
    28вҶ’* [Preprocessors] can provide extensions for custom syntax and modifying content
    29вҶ’* [Backends] can render the output to multiple formats
    30вҶ’* Written in [Rust] for speed, safety, and simplicity
    31вҶ’* Automated testing of [Rust code samples]
    32вҶ’
    33вҶ’This guide is an example of what mdBook produces.
    34вҶ’mdBook is used by the Rust programming language project, and [The Rust Programming Language][trpl] book is another fine example of mdBook in action.
    35вҶ’
    36вҶ’[Markdown]: format/markdown.md
    37вҶ’[search]: guide/reading.md#search
    38вҶ’[syntax highlighting]: format/theme/syntax-highlighting.md
