   159вҶ’## Configuration
   160вҶ’
   161вҶ’Now imagine you don't want to count the number of words on a particular chapter
   162вҶ’(it might be generated text/code, etc). The canonical way to do this is via the
   163вҶ’usual `book.toml` configuration file by adding items to your `[output.foo]`
   164вҶ’table.
   165вҶ’
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   219вҶ’## Output and signalling failure
   220вҶ’
   221вҶ’While it's nice to print word counts to the terminal when a book is built, it
   222вҶ’might also be a good idea to output them to a file somewhere. `mdbook` tells a
   223вҶ’backend where it should place any generated output via the `destination` field
   224вҶ’in [`RenderContext`].
   225вҶ’
      вҶ’вҖҰ
   322вҶ’## Wrapping up
   323вҶ’
   324вҶ’Although contrived, hopefully this example was enough to show how you'd create
   325вҶ’an alternative backend for `mdbook`. If you feel it's missing something, don't
   326вҶ’hesitate to create an issue in the [issue tracker] so we can improve the user
   327вҶ’guide.
   328вҶ’
